SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13
14
in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 5072 of Title 63, unless there
14
15
is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15
16
A. The Oklahoma Health Care Authority shall not require, as a
16
17
condition of participation in the state Medicaid program, a provider
17
18
to submit an attestation or other document disclosing whether the
18
19
provider performs, refers for, or is affiliated with any entity that
19
20
performs abortions including, but not limited to, by requiring such
20
21
attestation or document as a condition of:
21
22
1. Contracting with the Authority or any contracted entity for
22
23
Medicaid services;
23
24
2. Receiving payment for Medicaid services; or
24
